	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p>Original</p>
			<p>O<add>&#63;</add> Rosalie &#40;Duplicate&#41; <hi rend="indent(1)"></hi><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> A H <date>Ab. 5604</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isc Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Since my last of <date>13th</date> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> <add>&#63;</add> Brig Duca<add>&#63;</add> via Ponce&#44; I have been presented<lb/> attending to my business owing the severe <add>&#63;</add><lb/> &#61;sequent death of my beloved wife <persName>Grace Sarah</persName><lb/> was taken from me on the <date>16th</date> day<add>&#63;</add> of <date>Janry</date> in her <add>&#63;</add><lb/> year. her sickness was Consumption&#8212;I must yield<lb/> with resignation altho&#39; the loss is very great&#44; I have <add>&#63;</add><lb/> with 2 daughters.  The will of God be done&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours of <date>May 17th</date> &#38; <date>June 11th</date> are at hand with books<lb/> all correct&#44; I enclose herewith first of summoned<add>&#63;</add><lb/> 16.00 <add>&#63;</add> at 10 <add>&#63;</add> on the <persName>Mrss.Atwater</persName> <add>&#63;</add> <placeName>New York</placeName> for<lb/> One hundred dollars which please pass to my credit <add>&#63;</add><lb/> the capt of the &#8220;Rosalie&#8221; will take freight I will send the<lb/> Bay Water required&#44; please have a plate engraved<lb/> at last for <persName>D Alverty</persName> and send 300 cards with the<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> always retaining the plate.  <add>&#63;</add><lb/> been suspended &#38; I believe will never ascend the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <placeName>St Thomas</placeName> <add>&#63;</add> Hazan he has worked is own <add>&#63;</add><lb/> charge against him are very serious at the <add>Hebrew</add> <add>&#63;</add> poor<lb/> wife he refused to call her by my name&#44; &#38; called her by<lb/> her fathers name&#44; giving us his <add>&#63;</add></p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>I have not yet received one cent on Acct of the<lb/> 2nd Vol of the Occident.  Please add on the rest of<lb/> subscribers <persName>Mr A Senior</persName> of <placeName>Aguadilla</placeName> P<add>&#63;</add> &#38; <persName>Mr<lb/> Hy Helmann</persName> of <placeName>Angostura</placeName> both for the 2nd Volume.<lb/>  I hope soon to obtain more.  take off <persName>Mr O<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> The Rosalie does not take freight&#8212;the 2 dozen<lb/> spelling books are gone to <placeName>Cura&#231;ao</placeName>&#8212;I want more.<lb/>  The information from <placeName>Cura&#231;ao</placeName> &#38; the main has<lb/> not yet reached me.  I anticipate getting some<lb/> purchasers for the Per<add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>A Wolff</persName> has resigned as President because<lb/> he finds that his darling Idol <persName>Carrillon</persName> is op<lb/> &#61;posed by the majority of the community.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Without further subject I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">M B Simmons</persName></p>
				<p><date>July 19</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The foregoing is duplicate of my last.<lb/> I want some &#8220;Cathecisms&#8221; &#38; first books for<lb/> young children easier than the Cathecisms.</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">MBS</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><addressee>Revd Isc Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><add>&#63;</add> Emily</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">via <placeName>N York</placeName></p>
